assets could have been used to pay off creditors instead coalco was transferred to the parent company dynegy inc where creditors could not get access to itreduced to its essence the transaction transferred hundreds of millions of dollars away from dynegys creditors in favor of its stockholders kirpalani wrote in his reportkirpalani said that some directors on dynegys board did not understand the nature of the transaction that shifted coalco from one unit to another but others knew exactly what was happening and why the coalco transfer was being madedynegy released a brief statement saying the company is reviewing the report a spokeswoman said the company is determining how the finding might affect the bankruptcy proceedingthe houston company operates power plants and sells electricity on the open market it has struggled for years with falling electricity prices and infighting among investors over competing takeover offers and its credit ratings have sufferedas debts rose last year dynegy worked behind the scenes to protect the company instead of selling assets to raise cash the company reshuffled its businesses so that the parent company owned power plants and other assets while a subsidiary issued bonds bondholders sued in september alleging that dynegy illegally protected some assets from claims they could make in bankruptcy courtdynegy holdings llc and four of its subsidiaries filed for bankruptcy protection on nov  with a plan to restructure  billion in debtshares fell  cents or  percent to  cents in afternoon trading they closed at  on nov popular in the communityman says he killed wife aboard cruise ship because she would not stop laughing at me affidavit reactionswomen need to carry this device with themsiren songsponsoreddozens injured in barcelona commuter train crash reactionstrump administration reportedly threatens alaska over senator’s health care vote reactionsmario cantone perfectly captures trump’s new bff anthony scaramucci reactionszuckerberg wifes